##When will the awakening of insects in the Book Industry Come?

WECHAT BooksAndFun

Features, here, with the best quality of cultural original content encounter.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
"there is no end to the epidemic. The bookstore can not hold on. " On February 24, one-way space issued a letter of life-saving, said the impact of the new crown disease, bookstore revenue in February fell 80% compared to previous years, hope to launch 50 yuan to 8,000 yuan crowdfunding assistance program. The move drew criticism from the "book-making" public, with an article titled "Can one-way space be saved only by emotional recharge? " Accusing one-way spaces such as online red bookstores of coming out to save at this time, instead, it overdraws Wenqing's wallet, leaving more independent bookstores in urban communities and "desert oases" in second, third and fourth-tier cities without attention.

The reason for the hidden worry of "overdrawing Wenqing Wallets" is that under the long epidemic situation of more than a month, both online bookstores in big cities and small bookstores in second, third and fourth-tier cities have no customers and sales have stagnated, have taken a variety of measures to try to save themselves. In fact, not only the bookstore, the entire book industry in all sectors affected by the epidemic, including the physical bookstore was the most serious and obvious impact.

First, the biggest difficulty online bookstores face is that most of their warehouses have not returned to work and can not deliver, according to an interview with ID: Booksandfun. COM, which launched an "88 yuan optional 10 copies" campaign to address cash flow problems. Second, large e-commerce companies such as Dangdang, while claiming that book sales have not been affected, are also causing panic among consumers as some employees are diagnosed with new pneumonia. Third, brick-and-mortar bookstores face a double test, on the one hand, the old problems remain -- as if e-commerce has already beaten the hell out of brick-and-mortar bookstores, and state and capital subsidies have failed to help bookstores enhance their own hematopoiesis. On the other hand, new opportunities are emerging, more and more bookstores are experimenting with online activities, live streaming, online crowdfunding, and other ways to survive the epidemic.

China Book Network Launches "88 yuan optional 10" activity

In response to the current plight of brick-and-mortar bookstores, the government introduced a number of related measures. For example, on February 26, the Publicity Department of the Beijing Municipal Party Committee issued a notice on the support work of the entity bookstores in Beijing in 2020, and coordinated the publishing units to provide more convenience and support to the entity bookstores in the areas of book supply, Refund Period, marketing activities, etc. , propose to extend the payback period for 3-6 months; coordinate the e-commerce platform to waive or reduce the occupancy fee of the bookstore, and give special rate concessions and flow subsidies. Can the book industry survive the cold winter with both policy and self-help efforts?

1
Press:
The double-edged Sword of free or low-cost open resources

On Feb. 5, "Utopia" launched an online campaign inspired by photos of young people reading Fushan's "the origins of political order" at Wuhan's Shelter Hospital that went viral on social media, "See the ideal" and "the republic" have opened more than 1,300 episodes of programs and more than 20 e-books to listen to and read. Readers can listen to the show for free with the ideal APP, or pick up more than 20 e-books at the book's flagship store for 1 yuan each. In a similar vein, the Commercial Press, which offers free access to thousands of e book resources, and its English World magazine has a deadline to make all of its e book content free. Huacheng Publishing House in the "love Guangzhou" APP in the form of free reading for a total of 19 years, "Huacheng" magazine e-version.

Young people read Fushan's the origin of political order at the Shelter Hospital in Wuhan

Xiao Yanbing, editor-in-chief of southern publishing media and President of Huacheng Publishing House, told interface culture that on the one hand, by launching these free initiatives, he hopes to play the role of literature in soothing pain and inspiring people, reflect due responsibility, on the other hand also let flower city attracted more readers. After the free and open reading resources, the amount of literature read on the platform of "Love Guangzhou" has greatly increased, and the Electronic Music Teaching Materials of Huacheng Publishing House are downloaded hundreds of thousands of times every day. From an objective point of view, the epidemic more clear "publishing integration" of the development trend, but also more determined to do a digital publishing Huacheng press.

But publishing houses opening up free or low-cost resources is also a "double-edged sword. ". He Huiying, president and editor-in-chief of Shandong Friendship Publishing House, said in an interview with Baidao.com that free sharing by the publishing house can play a good role in advertising and publicity, laying a foundation for the hot sale of paper books in the future. However, for some books, it is also possible that overdraft of book content will affect the sale of paper books, "unconditional free online sharing in times of emergency fully reflects the responsibility of state-owned cultural enterprises, but it may not be affordable for most publishing houses to share it for free in the long run. "

But in the paper book's publication and the pricing aspect, the publishing house is still in the restricted condition generally. Xiao Yanbing in an interview with the network, Huacheng Publishing House Book Publishing and Production and sales have been affected by the epidemic. In the area of publishing, as most printing enterprises use workers in the off-peak season, the epidemic may affect their daily use of workers, printing schedule affected, paper and printing costs may also increase a lot. In the sales segment, more than 90% of the ground-based brick-and-mortar bookstores are closed, and online sales have been hit hard by the lack of logistics, while the sale of paper books is blocked both online and offline. The general manager of Commercial Press, Yu Dianli, pointed out the particularity of book pricing and the Dilemma Facing the publishing house in its current special situation. He argued that other categories of goods could be flexibly priced according to cost before being put on shelves, whereas books had been priced and clearly labelled in previous production processes and prices could not be adjusted in response to increased costs, last-minute price changes raise questions among readers.

" On February 24, one-way space issued a letter of life-saving, said the impact of the new crown disease, bookstore revenue in February fell 80% compared to previous years, hope to launch 50 yuan to 8,000 yuan crowdfunding assistance program. The move drew criticism from the "book-making" public, with an article titled "Can one-way space be saved only by emotional recharge? " Accusing one-way spaces such as online red bookstores of coming out to save at this time, instead, it overdraws Wenqing's wallet, leaving more independent bookstores in urban communities and "desert oases" in second, third and fourth-tier cities without attention.

The reason for the hidden worry of "overdrawing Wenqing Wallets" is that under the long epidemic situation of more than a month, both online bookstores in big cities and small bookstores in second, third and fourth-tier cities have no customers and sales have stagnated, have taken a variety of measures to try to save themselves. In fact, not only the bookstore, the entire book industry in all sectors affected by the epidemic, including the physical bookstore was the most serious and obvious impact.

First, the biggest difficulty online bookstores face is that most of their warehouses have not returned to work and can not deliver, according to an interview with ID: Booksandfun. COM, which launched an "88 yuan optional 10 copies" campaign to address cash flow problems. Second, large e-commerce companies such as Dangdang, while claiming that book sales have not been affected, are also causing panic among consumers as some employees are diagnosed with new pneumonia. Third, brick-and-mortar bookstores face a double test, on the one hand, the old problems remain -- as if e-commerce has already beaten the hell out of brick-and-mortar bookstores, and state and capital subsidies have failed to help bookstores enhance their own hematopoiesis. On the other hand, new opportunities are emerging, more and more bookstores are experimenting with online activities, live streaming, online crowdfunding, and other ways to survive the epidemic.

E-COMMERCE PLATFORM:
Warehouse pressure and logistics obstacle

"I was wondering if I could return the book I just bought. "
"I just bought it. Return it and return it. "

That was the reaction on social media when news broke that Dangdang employees had been diagnosed with a new case of pneumonia. Although Dangdang customer service tried patiently to explain the library out of the non-contact and disinfection process, but still some consumers said that dare not buy books in Dangdang.

Unlike publishers, which actively organize online activities, e-commerce should have had an advantage in the epidemic. Indeed, the SARS epidemic of 2003 triggered a revolution in China's retail sector. Liu Qiangdong mentioned the closure of Zhongguancun's computer stores during the SARS outbreak, which led him to seriously consider becoming an e-commerce business and eventually to go full online. As soon as SARS broke out, Jack Ma also perceived that online shopping would become a just-in-time need for consumers, and it was necessary for Alibaba to launch a 2C (for ordinary consumers) online shopping platform on top of the 2B (for corporate customers) business that existed at that time. On May 10,2003, Taobao launched and soon defeated the American internet giant Ebay, which was thriving in China. Normally, the outbreak would seem to be spurring the growth of online shopping, but this time around, some online bookstores in China are not immune to the winter.

Dangdang officials say the 100-50 campaign is not being launched because books are not being sold during the outbreak, but because it is a regular event during the school year. When Dangdang said the current book "sales are normal, " but the interface culture reporter also found that the current online book prescription can not guarantee, much slower than normal delivery speed, such as February 27 to buy the book is expected to be delivered a week later, the logistics problem is real.

Compared with Dangdang, other online bookstores are facing a much tougher situation. If you open the China books website, your attention will be attracted by the huge advertisement "88 yuan 10 books" in the front page of the website. The website even went on Weibo to search for 6,000 books for 88 yuan, covers literature, social sciences, history, children, art and other categories, but the warehouse after the resumption of shipments. In a Feb. 12 post on Weibo, China's micro-blogging site, CNTU spoke of the huge pressure facing the warehouse -- "The warehouse in Zhuozhou has not yet resumed and there is no exact time to start construction, but the rent is still due, so we are trying to save ourselves, " CNTU's general manager Huangping told Beijing Art Review, "without the money, we would have a cash flow problem, " the successful promotion helped CTO pay staff salaries and end-of-year bonuses before the Lunar New Year and set aside some cash for post-holiday operations.

Chinanews.com

The biggest difficulties for online bookstores are the fact that most warehouses are not working, unable to ship, and the logistics are poor. In the report of "Beiqing Art Review" , "In this outbreak, the more large online bookstores, the greater the difficulties encountered, " said an anonymous publisher. "One of our important customers, in addition to the national online sales, there are more than a dozen brick-and-mortar bookstores, but the warehouse in Hubei, because delivery from Hubei to all parts of the country, the price is cheaper, this all fall. He says it's still operational, but the warehouse is closed and he can't ship it. I thought he was going to cry."

Brick and mortar bookstores:
It's not easy to survive, to save yourself

"Across the book industry, publishers are losing less, online bookstores are losing more, and brick-and-mortar bookstores are losing the most, " Huangping said. Shumeng, an alliance of small and medium-sized bookstores, conducted an emergency survey of brick-and-mortar bookstores for the Spring Festival in 2020. The survey report reflects the current situation of small and medium-sized private bookstores in the midst of the epidemic. Among the 353 valid questionnaires nationwide, 86. ninety-seven per cent of bookstores currently have almost no source of income. If the epidemic continues, 34.56 per cent of bookstores will last less than a month. Some bookstores are already closing, while 40 per cent say they will not last more than three months.

Survey data of "Shu Meng" in the Alliance of small and medium-sized bookstores

Sangeng bookstore in Chaozhou, Guangdong Province, is one of the closing bookstores. In October 2017, one of the partners, Yao Chaofan, returned to Chaozhou in the context of the store's recovery, and for two years tried a combination of bookstore and restaurant, barely able to maintain operations. He had thought this year would be a revival of the bookstore, but now he had to write a farewell letter in the public address "Three Watch missed the appointment" : "floating life is very hard to run, the grand feast ended. "

Wan Guoying, the founder of Qingyuan Bookstore in Nanchang, saw some of the publishers'plans for free online sharing as well as the 50-percent-off top promotion launched by United Dangdang. She worries that "when people see too much free stuff, they won't feel the need to spend any more" , and has a vague hunch that the industry will once again be in a free-for-all to digest its inventory. She understands that at this point every business wants to protect itself and get cash flow to cover its expenses, but as a result, the market could end up in the Red Sea of discounts. "readers are sure to go wherever is cheaper, but brick-and-mortar bookstores will suffer, " Wan told interface culture.

On January 31st, for the first time in its 28 year history, Qingyuan books issued a call for help on its public account. After the Article "I am Qingyuan Bookstore, please don't let me freeze to death in the wind and snow" was published, 200 readers recharged nearly 100,000 yuan in Qingyuan Bookstore. One way also launched a crowdfunding renewal campaign on Feb. 24, according to its official article. Currently, only one of the four brick and mortar bookstores in Beijing, Chaoyang Joy City, is open, selling an average of only 15 books a day, half of which are bought by colleagues. Although has tried online platform store value concessions, live online, Jianqun seconds kill a series of activities, but each promotion can only bring in a few hundred dollars. Its e-commerce platform because the supplier did not start, limited logistics and other reasons, sales almost halved.

Qingyuan Bookstore sends out a request for help on Wechat

Huang Yipin, special assistant to the general manager of Shanghai Zhongshu and vice president of Zhongshuge, told the interface culture that the physical bookstore of Zhongshuge also suffered a great impact during the epidemic, "In 2019, a total of 13 stores sold more than 5 million units in the half-month of the Spring Festival alone. Only three stores were open during the Spring Festival this year, with sales of less than 100,000 units. " Jing 'an stores have already opened, but only part of the area is open, with a maximum of forty passengers a day.

In addition, Zhong Shuge also began to try to live with goods. The first broadcast was watched by more than 8,000 people, and the new book, Professor Covid-19, sold more than 150 copies in an hour. In addition to tmall and Dangdang stores, the customer base in each store will also accept reader orders. Even if the rich self-help measures, the current entity bookstore is still part of the losses, but Huang Yiping, Bell Shuge at present and there is no "the epidemic continues to go down the company will go out of business" serious problem. Because Zhong Shuge head office Shanghai Zhong Shu has its own publishing business, and to extracurricular reading class student books, the guests are mainly students. This period of time although the children at home, but also still need to buy books, online book sales are relatively high.

Zhong shuge live broadcast

But offline non demand retail entities are much harder. According to Guangzhou Fuguang Bookstore (Shiguangli store) , the stores under the Fuguang Bookstore brand are facing a sharp drop in passenger flow, a backlog of inventory, and a small and single income, at the same time, we still have to pay the monthly suppliers'payment and rent (some shops have received the support of the owners to reduce rent) , as well as the wages of all the workers who have not reduced their wages or laid off their employees. Meanwhile, bookstores are increasingly worried about changes in consumer psychology and spending habits during the epidemic, as well as weak demand for print books in the future. Fukuoka said it expects publishers to make short-term adjustments to their loan books and to ease returns and offer incentives.

3

Brick and mortar bookstores:
It's not easy to survive, to save yourself

"Across the book industry, publishers are losing less, online bookstores are losing more, and brick-and-mortar bookstores are losing the most, " Huangping said. Shumeng, an alliance of small and medium-sized bookstores, conducted an emergency survey of brick-and-mortar bookstores for the Spring Festival in 2020. The survey report reflects the current situation of small and medium-sized private bookstores in the midst of the epidemic. Among the 353 valid questionnaires nationwide, 86. ninety-seven per cent of bookstores currently have almost no source of income. If the epidemic continues, 34.56 per cent of bookstores will last less than a month. Some bookstores are already closing, while 40 per cent say they will not last more than three months.

Survey data of "Shu Meng" in the Alliance of small and medium-sized bookstores

Sangeng bookstore in Chaozhou, Guangdong Province, is one of the closing bookstores. In October 2017, one of the partners, Yao Chaofan, returned to Chaozhou in the context of the store's recovery, and for two years tried a combination of bookstore and restaurant, barely able to maintain operations. He had thought this year would be a revival of the bookstore, but now he had to write a farewell letter in the public address "Three Watch missed the appointment" : "floating life is very hard to run, the grand feast ended. "

Wan Guoying, the founder of Qingyuan Bookstore in Nanchang, saw some of the publishers'plans for free online sharing as well as the 50-percent-off top promotion launched by United Dangdang. She worries that "when people see too much free stuff, they won't feel the need to spend any more" , and has a vague hunch that the industry will once again be in a free-for-all to digest its inventory. She understands that at this point every business wants to protect itself and get cash flow to cover its expenses, but as a result, the market could end up in the Red Sea of discounts. "readers are sure to go wherever is cheaper, but brick-and-mortar bookstores will suffer, " Wan told interface culture.

On January 31st, for the first time in its 28 year history, Qingyuan books issued a call for help on its public account. After the Article "I am Qingyuan Bookstore, please don't let me freeze to death in the wind and snow" was published, 200 readers recharged nearly 100,000 yuan in Qingyuan Bookstore. One way also launched a crowdfunding renewal campaign on Feb. 24, according to its official article. Currently, only one of the four brick and mortar bookstores in Beijing, Chaoyang Joy City, is open, selling an average of only 15 books a day, half of which are bought by colleagues. Although has tried online platform store value concessions, live online, Jianqun seconds kill a series of activities, but each promotion can only bring in a few hundred dollars. Its e-commerce platform because the supplier did not start, limited logistics and other reasons, sales almost halved.

Qingyuan Bookstore sends out a request for help on Wechat

Huang Yipin, special assistant to the general manager of Shanghai Zhongshu and vice president of Zhongshuge, told the interface culture that the physical bookstore of Zhongshuge also suffered a great impact during the epidemic, "In 2019, a total of 13 stores sold more than 5 million units in the half-month of the Spring Festival alone. Only three stores were open during the Spring Festival this year, with sales of less than 100,000 units. " Jing 'an stores have already opened, but only part of the area is open, with a maximum of forty passengers a day.

In addition, Zhong Shuge also began to try to live with goods. The first broadcast was watched by more than 8,000 people, and the new book, Professor Covid-19, sold more than 150 copies in an hour. In addition to tmall and Dangdang stores, the customer base in each store will also accept reader orders. Even if the rich self-help measures, the current entity bookstore is still part of the losses, but Huang Yiping, Bell Shuge at present and there is no "the epidemic continues to go down the company will go out of business" serious problem. Because Zhong Shuge head office Shanghai Zhong Shu has its own publishing business, and to extracurricular reading class student books, the guests are mainly students. This period of time although the children at home, but also still need to buy books, online book sales are relatively high.

Zhong shuge live broadcast

But offline non demand retail entities are much harder. According to Guangzhou Fuguang Bookstore (Shiguangli store) , the stores under the Fuguang Bookstore brand are facing a sharp drop in passenger flow, a backlog of inventory, and a small and single income, at the same time, we still have to pay the monthly suppliers'payment and rent (some shops have received the support of the owners to reduce rent) , as well as the wages of all the workers who have not reduced their wages or laid off their employees. 3
EPILOGUE: The Future of the bookstore

"these days, people are hiding at home and can't go out. I believe that when the epidemic is really over, there will be a wave of rebound in the bookstore, because after all, people are bored for a long time. People who like to read books just like to read books. Some People's leisure activities may be eating and going to play. Some people just want to go to the bookstore. I think there will be many customers who want to come back. " Huang is generally optimistic about the actual bookstore after the epidemic ends. She said that although the book is not just needed, but many people have to go to the bookstore to read books as a life in the spirit of sustenance.

Wan Guoying that the impact of the epidemic is still 1 to 2 months, bookstore recovery will take three months, six months to be able to see the changes in the industry. In the book industry as a whole, only books that are in demand or especially popular, such as tutoring, will become the focus of consumption. "people don't want spiritual needs until they have met their basic needs. Within six months, brick and mortar bookstores will fall, and those that survive will be in danger. Rent Relief, social security subsidies and other measures may be able to solve the problem of two or three months, but 'emergency relief can not help the poor' . "

The weakness of brick-and-mortar bookshops is not new, and the epidemic is simply tearing open old wounds in the industry. In an interview with interface culture, Wan said that e-commerce had beaten the brick-and-mortar bookstores to the ground before the outbreak. "The discount war has been going on since 2018. Last year it was even worse. There was almost monthly e-commerce activity, and in 2019 the figures for physical bookstores are already ugly. " In the physical bookstore industry, state subsidies and capital subsidies have distorted the survival of the industry, leading to the bookstore industry business model ambiguous. This is also one of the criticisms of the article "making books" on one-way space: The main product is a one-way calendar, and what moves the cultural world is the single-way magazine and the one-way Street Bookstore Literature Prize, might as well take off the "heavy body. ".

Qingyuan bookstore, Feb. 18, Via@qingyuan Bookstore

"Can a bookshop stand on its own two feet in a palatial setting? Not counting the investment, such a standard allocation also adds to the cost of service. "The profitability of books, coffee and literature can not be translated into the shop's blood-making function, but it can not really be a commercial activity if it is done entirely on subsidies, " said Wan, the government's policy and financial support is conducive to the development of the bookstore. But the bookstore industry should have a thought, because now many people as a book accessories and decorations, let the bookstore as a clock, photo, sightseeing place. "Peking University is not a good school because it has a lot of students, but because it has produced a lot of talents. The same is true of bookstores. What guidance they can bring to the public and how many seeds they can cultivate are the true meaning of their existence. "

If Wan is worried about the old problems of brick-and-mortar bookstores, Sun Qian, the founder of Book Meng, sees a new way out. In an interview with China News & Publication Radio & Telegraph, Sun said that the idea of "bookstore + " and "book + " , which had been popular in the bookstore industry, had been greatly challenged by the outbreak. How the entity bookstore runs through the entire operation of the Internet thinking, online and offline in line with the actual integration of the entity bookstore, will become the majority of the entity bookstore most concerned and practical direction. He later published an article titled how Physical Bookstores can be profitable -- the future, which claims that the future of physical bookstores depends on three main components: An upgraded product line, from selling only books, literature, coffee and other tangible products to expand to courses, knowledge, services and other intangible products; to upgrade services, from the original only to provide existing products of wholesale and retail services to provide social and emotional services; space to carry out offline to online upgrade, to accumulate a sense of trust to their customers, to form their own "private area flow. ". "The battle for the future of brick-and-mortar bookstores will no longer be just offline. The future, where products, services, and spaces all move online, is a new topic for everyone. "

Qingyuan Bookstore has also launched an online campaign, in the "Bookstore Lighting Program" , the bookstore sold less than 10 books, from a sales point of view is not very profitable. However, Wan Guoying see, do online activity itself is meaningful, can let in the epidemic period at home for a month of book friends get some new thinking. The future may bring new combinations online and offline, she said. On Feb. 20, Qingyuan Bookstore opened for business, with fewer than 20 customers on the first day and even fewer on the second. Still, wgb is hopeful, a frequent visitor tells her, that the outbreak is over and readers can get together again.

This is an exclusive, original story, written by Pan Wenjie, edited by Huang Yue, and can not be reproduced without the authorization of interface culture (ID: Booksandfun) .
